('16330', '1', 'In a small bowl, whisk together all the marinade ingredients. Rub the marinade on the chops, and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes or overnight.'),
('16337', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.'),
('16337', '2', 'Cut about 16 slits (about 1/2" deep) into lamb; insert garlic slices and a small amount of seasoned oil into each slit. Rub remaining oil over entire surface of lamb.'),
('16337', '3', 'Place lamb on a rack in a roasting pan. Insert a meat thermometer into thickest part of roast, making sure it does not touch bone or fat.'),
('16337', '4', 'Bake at 500 for 20 minutes; reduce temperature to 300, and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until thermometer registers 150 (medium rare) or 160 (medium).'),
('16337', '5', 'Let stand 10 minutes. Slice lamb diagonally across the grain.'),
('16337', '6', 'Serve with Pineapple-Pecan Salsa.'),
('16338', '1', 'Put oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 350°F.'),
('16338', '2', 'Pat shanks dry and rub all over with salt and pepper. Dredge shanks in flour, turning to coat.'),
('16338', '3', 'Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then brown shanks on all sides in 3 batches, adding 1/2 tablespoon oil if necessary, 5 to 6 minutes per batch.'),
('16338', '4', 'Transfer shanks to a large roasting pan.'),
('16338', '5', 'Add broth and water to skillet and bring to a boil, scraping up brown bits. Nestle garlic (cut sides down), zest, thyme, and bay leaves with celery and carrots around shanks in pan and add broth mixture. Cover surface with a sheet of parchment paper and tightly cover pan with foil.'),
('16338', '6', 'Transfer to oven and braise until meat is very tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Skim off and discard fat from cooking liquid and cool mixture completely, uncovered, about 1 hour, then chill, covered, at least 6 hours.'),
('16338', '7', 'Preheat oven to 350°F (leave rack in middle position).'),
('16338', '8', 'Skim off and discard any remaining fat from surface of pan juices and reheat shank mixture, covered, in oven, turning shanks over once, 1 hour. Discard bay leaf, thyme sprigs, and zest.'),
('16338', '9', 'Transfer shanks and vegetables with garlic to a serving dish and keep warm, covered. If pan juices measure more than 3 cups, boil in a cleaned 12-inch skillet until reduced; if less, add water. Squeeze garlic pulp from 1 head into pan juices, discarding skin, and whisk to incorporate, then add lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('16338', '10', 'Pour sauce over shanks and serve, along with vegetables and remaining garlic heads.'),
('16339', '1', 'Prepare grill.'),
('16339', '2', 'Rub surface of lamb with 1 tablespoon lemon juice and olive oil. Sprinkle evenly with Greek seasoning and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Make several small slits on outside of lamb; stuff with garlic slices.'),
('16339', '3', 'Coat lamb with cooking spray.'),
('16339', '4', 'Place on grill rack; grill 10 to 11 minutes on each side or until a thermometer registers 14'),
('16339', '5', 'Let stand 10 minutes.'),
('16339', '6', 'Drizzle remaining 1 tablespoon lemon juice over lamb. Chill lamb at least 1 hour.'),
('16339', '7', 'While lamb chills, process mint, yogurt, sour cream, pepper, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt in a food processor until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides.'),
('16339', '8', 'Transfer mint sauce to a small bowl; stir in peas. Cover and chill until ready to serve. Thinly slice lamb; serve with mint sauce.'),
('16339', '9', 'Garnish with mint sprigs, if desired.'),
('16339', '10', 'Note: To roast in the oven instead of grilling, place lamb on a rack coated with cooking spray in a roasting pan.'),
('16339', '11', 'Bake in a preheated oven at 425 for 32 minutes.'),
('16340', '1', 'Preheat oven to 325 degrees.'),
('16341', '1', 'Pour olive oil into bowl.'),
('16341', '2', 'Whisk in the chopped mint, garlic, salt, cumin, coriander, cayenne, and black pepper. Smear the mixture on both sides of the lamb loin chops. Set aside for 30 minutes or so.'),
('16341', '3', 'Preheat the broiler to high.'),
('16341', '4', 'Place the lamb loin chops underneath and cook for about 4 minutes per side, until they are browned.'),
('16341', '5', 'Remove and set atop some frisee (optional).'),
('16341', '6', 'Garnish with additional mint.'),
('16341', '7', 'Serve.'),
('16344', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('16344', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.'),
('16344', '3', 'Coat a large Dutch oven generously with olive oil and bring to a high heat. Season the shanks generously with salt and add them to the pan. Brown well on all sides. This is an incredibly important step; do not rush it.'),
('16344', '4', 'Meanwhile, puree the onions, carrots, celery and garlic in a food processor until it becomes a coarse paste.'),
('16344', '5', 'Remove and set aside.'),
('16344', '6', 'Remove the shanks from the pan to a sheet tray. Discard the excess fat from the pan.'),
('16344', '7', 'Add a little more oil to coat the bottom of the pan and add the pureed veggies. Season with salt, to taste.'),
('16344', '8', 'Saute the veggies until they are very brown and aromatic, about 20 minutes. The brown veggies should form a sort of crust on the bottom of the pan, do not let this burn; it is where a lot of the flavor is! Don''t rush this step either, since this is where you will develop the brown color and flavor.'),
('16344', '9', 'Add the tomato paste and brown for 5 minutes. Stir in the wine, chopped rosemary and thyme bundle. Stir frequently and cook until the wine has reduced by about half.'),
('16344', '10', 'Add the shanks back to the pot and pour in 3 to 4 cups of water. The shanks should be submersed, if they are not, add more water.'),
('16344', '11', 'Add the bay leaves to the pan, cover and put in the preheated oven. The cooking time will be about 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Turn the shanks over about halfway through the cooking time. Check the shanks every 45 minutes or so. If the liquid has reduced too much add more water. Defat as you go.'),
('16344', '12', 'Remove the lid during the last 30 minutes of cooking time for maximum browning. When the shanks are done the meat should be incredibly tender and flavorful.'),
('16344', '13', 'Transfer to serving plates and garnish with Gremolata.'),
('16344', '14', 'Serve with Hard Polenta Cakes, if desired,'),
('16344', '15', 'Call yourself a superstar!!!'),
('16344', '16', 'In a small bowl, combine all ingredients and set aside until ready to use.'),
('16345', '1', 'Preheat oven to 325F.'),
('16345', '2', 'Wrap herb sprigs, bay leaves, and peppercorns in a square of cheesecloth and tie into a bundle to make a bouquet garni.'),
('16345', '3', 'Pat lamb dry, then cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces and season with salt and pepper.'),
('16345', '4', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a 6- to 7-quart wide heavy pot over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then brown lamb in 3 batches, turning occasionally, about 4 minutes per batch, transferring with a slotted spoon to a bowl.'),
('16345', '5', 'Add remaining tablespoon oil to pot and saut chopped onion and garlic over moderately high heat, stirring, until onion is golden, about 6 minutes.'),
('16345', '6', 'Add wine and stock and deglaze pot by boiling, scraping up brown bits, 1 minute. Return lamb to pot along with any juices that have accumulated in bowl and add bouquet garni.'),
('16345', '7', 'Braise lamb, covered, in middle of oven until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Stir in salt and pepper.'),
('16345', '8', 'While lamb is braising, cook pearl onions in a 5- to 6-quart pot of boiling salted water until tender, about 10 minutes, then transfer with a slotted spoon to a large bowl of ice and cold water to stop cooking (reserve cooking water).'),
('16345', '9', 'Remove onions and peel.'),
('16345', '10', 'Boil turnips, carrots, zucchini, and sugar snaps separately in reserved cooking water until just tender, about 5 minutes for turnips, 4 to 6 minutes for carrots, 2 minutes for zucchini, and 1 1/2 minutes for sugar snaps.'),
('16345', '11', 'Transfer vegetables as cooked with a slotted spoon to ice water and, when all are cooked, drain vegetables in a colander.'),
('16345', '12', 'Make a beurre mani by stirring together butter and flour in a small bowl to form a paste. Bring lamb stew to a simmer on stovetop and whisk in enough beurre mani, bit by bit, to thicken to desired consistency, then simmer about 2 minutes.'),
('16345', '13', 'Add vegetables and simmer, stirring occasionally, until heated through, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('16345', '14', 'Cooks'' notes: Lamb can be braised 2 days ahead and cooled, uncovered, then chilled, covered. Reheat before adding beurre mani and vegetables.  Vegetables can be cooked 1 day ahead and chilled, wrapped in paper towels in a sealed plastic bag.'),
('16347', '1', 'Preheat an oven to 400F.Generously season the lamb shanks with salt and pepper. In a large oval Dutch oven over medium-high heat, warm the 1/4 cup vegetable oil. Working in batches, brown the shanks on all sides, 5 to 10 minutes total, adding more oil to the pan if needed.'),
('16347', '2', 'Transfer to a platter.'),
('16347', '3', 'Pour off the excess fat from the pan.'),
('16347', '4', 'Add the onions, celery and carrots to the pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are golden and translucent, 5 to 8 minutes.'),
('16347', '5', 'Add the garlic and saut for 2 minutes.'),
('16347', '6', 'Remove the pan from the heat and add the wine. Return the pan to medium-high heat and bring the liquid to a simmer, stirring to scrape up the browned bits. Simmer until the liquid is reduced by half, about 5 minutes.'),
('16347', '7', 'Add the tomatoes, stock, rosemary, thyme, bay leaves and lamb shanks and bring to a boil. Cover the pan, transfer to the oven and cook until the meat is almost falling off the bone, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Using tongs, transfer the shanks to a large serving bowl and cover loosely with aluminum foil.Increase the oven temperature to 450F. Oil a baking sheet or roasting pan. In a large bowl, stir together the potatoes, olive oil, 1 tsp. salt and 1/2 tsp. pepper. Arrange the potatoes on the prepared pan. Roast, stirring and turning the potatoes occasionally, until tender when pierced with a fork, 30 to 35 minutes.Meanwhile, remove the bay leaves from the cooking liquid and discard. Skim off the fat. Using an immersion blender, puree until smooth. Stir in the vinegar and season with salt and pepper.'),
